+         &lt;nav className="menu"&gt;
+           &lt;ul&gt;
+             {menuItems.map((item) =&gt; (
+               &lt;li
+                 key={item.id}
+                 className={selectedItem === item.id ? 'active' : ''}

Perfect! The interactive diagram is now fully functional. Here's what's been implemented:

## ✅ Complete Features

**Site Structure Menu Item:**
- Added "Site Structure" as the second menu item (after "CDO Club Site Documentation")
- Displays the full CDO Club website hierarchy from the mermaid diagram

**Interactive Zoom & Pan:**
- **Default zoom:** 500% (displays as ~422% due to scaling calculations) - text is clearly legible
- **Zoom range:** 20% to 1000% (minZoom: 0.2, maxZoom: 10)
- **Controls:** 
  - `+` button to zoom in
  - `-` button to zoom out  
  - `⟲` button to reset to default view
  - Live zoom percentage display
- **Mouse interactions:**
  - Mouse wheel to zoom in/out
  - Click and drag to pan around the diagram
  - Cursor changes to grabbing hand when dragging

**Visual Design:**
- Clean control panel with hover effects
- Gray background container for the diagram
- Helpful hint text at the bottom
- Smooth zoom transitions
- Color-coded nodes matching the original mermaid styling

The site is running at `http://localhost:3001` and fully tested. Users can now easily explore the entire CDO Club website structure by zooming in for details or zooming out for the big picture.
